  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2004-03-04",
    "date": "2004-07-29T16:17:46Z",
    "text": "Pell Grants Plus Act - Amends the Higher Education Act of 1965 (HEA) to direct the Secretary of Education to establish a program to award Pell Grants Plus grants to students who: (1) have completed a rigorous secondary school program for State Scholars; (2) are enrolled full-time in their first year of undergraduate education; and (3) are eligible to receive Federal Pell Grants for that year.\n\nSets such Plus grant award at $1,000. Provides for a continuation award for the second year of undergraduate education if the student maintains compliance with certain eligibility requirements and obtains a grade point average of at least 3.0 for the first year.\n\nRepeals HEA provisions for Academic Achievement Incentive Scholarships."
  },
